  <Subject Subject_ID="300015641">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300121293</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>derivative objects [300121293], object genres by original and derivative [300235003], object genres (object classifications) [300185712], Object Genres (hierarchy name) [300185711], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Valued objects or documents that are made or altered with intent to deceive; may range in falsehood from counterfeiting of whole works to altering of signatures or other deliberate misrepresentations. Distinguished from "copies (derivative objects)" by the intention of deception.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000030761/Oxford Companion to Art (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para objetos o documentos valiosos que que se hacen o se alteran con la intención de engañar; el rango del engaño puede ir desde falsificar la obra completa a alterar firmas u otra impostura deliberada. Se distingue de "copia” (objetos derivados) por la intención de estafa.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor gewilde objecten of documenten die worden gemaakt of veranderd om te misleiden; het bedrog kan uiteenlopen van de vervalsing van een heel werk tot het wijzigen van een handtekening of andere zwendel. Wordt onderscheiden van 'kopieën (afgeleide objecten)' door de opzet te misleiden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wertvolles Objekt oder Dokument, das mit einer Täuschungsabsicht hergestellt oder verändert wurde, wobei die Täuschung von der Fälschung ganzer Werke bis zur Veränderung von Unterschriften oder anderen vorsätzlichen Falschdarstellungen reichen kann. Zu unterscheiden von ["Kopie (abgeleitetes Objekt"](300015640) durch die Täuschungsabsicht.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以欺騙爲意圖而製造或改造的珍貴物件或文件；偽造的範圍包括從仿造整件作品，到修改簽名或其他蓄意的虛假呈現等。與「副本（衍生物件）」不同之處即在於其有欺騙之意圖。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
